properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued January 15 at 5:53PM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX
properties.description:
Moist onshore flow will continue to produce fog along the
nearshore waters and coastal areas this afternoon. Visibilities
will generally range from 2 to 5 nautical miles, with patchy
dense fog of 1 nautical mile or less at times. Widespread dense
fog may redevelop tonight, but with warming water temperatures
will wait to issue advisory until it does.

Mariners over the Bay Waters and over the Nearshore Coastal
Waters within 20 nautical miles offshore are urged to prepare for
rapidly changing visibilities.

NWSheadline: PATCHY DENSE FOG POSSIBLE AGAIN TONIGHT
